text: Im confused
They are crowdfunding a set review?
yes
Because they want to do it in person
Together
I too had that reaction Don
Then rolled my eyes
Wait wtf the more i read the more confused i am
They are going to do a 1.5 day set review??
They're doing the crowdfund so they can record it at the same location
Use the money to fly to Orlando it looks like
Yarp
WT fcuk
Shit lets crowdfund our next gpvegas instead of me laundering cash with magic singles
They're over $3k
In like, 24 hours too
Actually, Don, if people will pay for it, why *don't* we crowd fund it?
I’ve always felt like content producers asking for more money to produce content they would have produced anyways was super skeezy
Funds encourage growth or evolution of quality
I make all of my videos and stream essentially for free but if people were willing to throw money at me, I would upgrade my computer / recording equipment / video editing software once I had enough
So if we did a kickstarter to "Help bring new Commander 2018 content" to the site you'd think nothing of it?
Right, that's a little different than asking for MORE money than you already get to do something that you were going to do regardless though.
I mean, I think Patreon is for sustained content, kickstarter is for projects

If Don legit said "let's start a kickstarter to fund EDHRECVegas" I think people would give money for that. If Don started a patreon to support the site and maybe help hire more writers, more data folks, upgrade and maintain the site, whatever, I think people would do that, too
But if we were going to do Vegas already, would that not feel a little odd?
Not if you're doing it bigger and better than last year
And Don just said "I won't launder cash with singles", so you're not just doing the same, you're saving someone from spending their personal resources to do something with the public
If we're talking about just kickstarter going to Vegas, then maybe that's weird, but if you're talking about kickstarter'ing an EDHREC-sponsored event, that's different
I may have missed details of the conversation :stuck_out_tongue:

I'm just talking about asking for money to do something that you already were going to do and had planned. We know Magic Mics were going to do a Ravnica review. But crowdfunding it to do what they already were going to do(let's be honest, they probably would have gotten together in person for it regardless) and asking for people to pay for it just...
Just subsidize your Vegas trip by dancing a couple of nights at Wild Boyz
Don't forget, people were okay with giving their money, so does it really matter?
They were ok with asking for the money too
If it was worth doing, wouldn't their sponsor have offered to pay for it?
Out of budget maybe
So again, if it was worth doing, they would have found space in the budget.
Maybe that's just me having been in marketing for a while
I've seen tons of projects not have funds available
Sometimes you can't "find" money that does not exist
Hell, they could have done it to CUT costs
Maybe it was a profit thing
Is that wrong? Content creation for profit?
If the goal is to profit, but your content isn't making a profit...
Is it worth doing?
Depends. You're never gonna make a profit starting out
I mean, you do have to operate in the red to a degree. It's not like your mic pays for itself
Then there's hosting, etc.

If a project isn't making money and it's supposed to, usually the project gets cut. If it's a labor of love wouldn't they just do it regardless or go into the personal piggy bank. But asking for money to do what you want even if you have been told(we don't know about their sponsor situation obviously, this is just spitballing)  there isn't money to do it and you don't want to spend the money yourself, it just seems off...
Yeah
Magic Mic's isn't just starting off though

Our goal w CMDR Central was to be revenue neutral at least by year one. We knew starting up we'd have hardware costs and we'd eat hosting for awhile, etc. but we wanted to finish year one with the show paying it's way going forward

Iunno, I don't know how else to say that it doesn't seem off to me at all, but most of my experience is with military budgeting, so we never have money but we have to do things, so when we submit unfunded requests or even ask other organizations for money, we don't hesitate
I think the scale of importance between military spending/projects and content production is a little uneven though
Maybe. I have issues not thinking military-ish in everything I do, though
Praetor Magic has a mission statement, for example
We don't have to agree, I'm just explaining why I think it's dumb to crowdfund
Projects like this at least
Sure, if you don't have a mission statement/direction you're just spinning your wheels. I agree with that
If I told my wife that my travel, food and lodging to Vegas was covered it would be a lot easier to get her to say yes, is all I'm saying.
I don't make a ton of money doing what I do, and we're looking at getting a house next year, so money is going to be getting tightish.
Maybe that's just me.
Pft, I'm in the military, I barely make money :stuck_out_tongue:
What's money?
They pay me in government assistance
Yeah, there's no way my family would (or could) fund a Vegas trip for me to play mtg
Command zone likely isn't doing a party never year at Vegas so we should
Now, if I was single with no kids I would totally hitch hike and couch surf my way to Vegas.
If you pay to go to Vegas on your own you could be single again…
Is that an unethical life hack?
In general i dont like asking for money wih kickstarter or whatever
I dont like owing people shit
Also i can say that EDHREC’s progress is limited less by money as of a few months ago and more just attention span from me
Id pay for a vegas party if someone planned it and did a good job
